gomodel:SYNGO_1822  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5 A cell surface interaction screen identifies PTPδ as binder of the IL-1RAcP ECD\nFig.6 The ECD of IL-1RAcP and IL-1RAcPb bind the PTPδ ECD\n\nAuthors note:\n- Adhesion is measured in a cell aggregation assay on a sensor chip.\n- The referenced figures show adhesive properties in non-neuronal cells. The functional relevance for synapse formation between these pre- and postsynaptic proteins is represented in other tickets based on this paper.. Experimental description: - Overexpressed 1RAcP is of mouse species: \"The entire coding sequences of mouse IL-1RAcP, IL-1RAcPb, ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-02" ;
